  "summary": "npmkekw ships base64-decoded TCP payload in misc/tcp.js",
  "details": "The package contains misc/tcp.js which uses Buffer.from(..., 'base64').toString(...) to decode embedded base64 blobs. The file name and the base64-decode-then-execute shape are characteristic of a hidden TCP backdoor / reverse-shell loader rather than any documented package functionality. Decoding base64 strings into runtime code or network payloads inside a file named tcp.js, in a package with no legitimate networking purpose, hides the actual behavior from casual review and is consistent with embedded malicious code.",
